<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB7FFDAFCF7F964FDDFFED5" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="278" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB7FFDAFCF7F964FDDFFED5" blockId="8.[824,1474,1730,1914]" lastBlockId="9.[113,763,279,335]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="278" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB7FFDBFCF7F964FA66F943" box="[862,1446,1730,1754]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">
Distribution and ecology. – 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB7FFDBFB36F964FA66F943" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1183,1446,1730,1754]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mouana">Lepidocupania mouana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is endemic to Grande Terre, where it is restricted to Mont Mou in the southwest. 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB7FFDBFC5EF8A4FB52F880" author="ADEMA, F." box="[1015,1170,1794,1818]" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" refId="ref11451" refString="ADEMA, F. (1991). Cupaniopsis Radlk. (Sapindaceae): a monograph. Leiden Bot. Ser. 15." type="book" year="1991">ADEMA (1991)</bibRefCitation>
cited a single specimen, the 
<typeStatus id="864231FDFFB7FFDBFC91F884FC56F8A0" box="[824,918,1826,1850]" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">holotype</typeStatus>
, collected in 1951, while an additional collection was made in 2009 (
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB7FFDBFC71F8E4FB2EF8C3" box="[984,1262,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="277">Grignon &amp; Munzinger 256</emphasis>
). This species grows in continuous tall maquis (“maquis paraforestier”, see 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB7FFDAFAC5F8C4FF25FEB5" author="MCCOY, S. G. &amp; JAFFRE, F." lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="278" pageId="8" pageNumber="277" pagination="579 - 594" refId="ref12158" refString="MCCOY, S. G., T. JAFFRE, F. RIGAULT &amp; J. E. ASH (1999). Fire and succession in the ultramafic maquis of New Caledonia. J. Biogeog. 26: 579 - 594." type="journal article" year="1999">MCCOY et al., 1999</bibRefCitation>
for details) dominated by species of 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB6FFDAFDDCFEB1FED6FED5" authority="L. A. S. Johnson" authorityName="L. A. S. Johnson" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Gymnostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB6FFDAFDDCFEB1FD3BFEB4" box="[629,763,279,302]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">Gymnostoma</emphasis>
L.A.S. Johnson
</taxonomicName>
, on peridotitic substrate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB6FFDAFF3EFEDEFD3EFE35" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB6FFDAFF3EFEDEFD3EFE35" blockId="9.[113,766,375,431]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB6FFDAFF3EFEDEFE04FE15" box="[151,452,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="278">
Note. – 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB6FFDAFF4BFED1FE04FE15" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[226,452,375,399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mouana">Lepidocupania mouana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was assigned an IUCN risk of extinction status of “Endangered” [EN] by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB6FFDAFD99FE34FD3AFE35" author="JAFFRE, T." box="[560,762,402,431]" pageId="9" pageNumber="278" pagination="109 - 135" refId="ref12116" refString="JAFFRE, T., P. BOUCHET &amp; J. M. VEILLON (1998). Threatened plants of New Caledonia: is the system of protected areas adequate? Biodivers. Conserv. 7: 109 - 135." type="journal article" year="1998">JAFFRÉ et al. (1998)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
